# Exotic India Integrations (`integrations/exotic/`)

All Exotic India HTTP clients live here. Do not add new cURL blocks in controllers.

## Layout

| Path | API base | Purpose |
|------|----------|---------|
| `vendor_api.php` | `https://www.exoticindia.com/vendor-api` | Product fetch/modify, order modify, group-fetch |
| `Clients/RetailApiClient.php` | `https://www.exoticindia.com/api` | POS cart, `/product/code`, `/order/create` |
| `Clients/OrderClient.php` | vendor-api | `/order/modify` |
| `Support/CartResponseParser.php` | — | Parse retail cart JSON success/messages |
| `Support/OrderResponseParser.php` | — | Parse order/create order number |
| `Support/RetailApiDeviceIdResolver.php` | — | `x-api-deviceid` from warehouse name |
| `ExoticIndiaGateway.php` | both | Facade: `create()`, `retail()`, order status sync |

## Usage

```php
// Retail (POS)
require_once 'integrations/exotic/Clients/RetailApiClient.php';
$retail = RetailApiClient::create($conn);
$res = $retail->call('/cart/retrieve', 'GET', $query, null, null, $extraHeaders);

// Vendor-api (legacy procedural — still supported)
require_once 'helpers/exotic_india_api.php'; // shim → integrations/exotic/vendor_api.php
$result = exotic_india_api_post('/order/modify', $postBody);

// Gateway (order status sync + retail accessor)
$gateway = ExoticIndiaGateway::create($conn);
$gateway->updateOrderLineFromSlug($slug, $orderRow);
$gateway->retail()->call('/product/code', 'GET', ['code' => $sku]);
```

## Rules

- **New retail endpoints** → `RetailApiClient::call()` only.
- **New vendor-api endpoints** → add to `vendor_api.php` or a new `Clients/*Client.php`.
- **Cart response parsing** → `CartResponseParser` (never duplicate in controllers).
- `helpers/exotic_india_api.php` is a **shim** — implement in `integrations/exotic/vendor_api.php`.
- `POSRegisterController::exotic_api_call()` is deprecated; delegates to `RetailApiClient`.
